Answer:
&lt;div class="post-text" itemprop="text"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I've had a good read through and found a class I didn't know existed before, which allows MongoDB to remember which class each object belongs to without having to explicitly set a type map. I changed my class objects that implemented &lt;code&gt;MongoDB\BSON\Serializable&lt;/code&gt; and &lt;code&gt;MongoDB\BSON\Unserializable&lt;/code&gt; to just implementing &lt;code&gt;MongoDB\BSON\Persistable&lt;/code&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;code&gt;MongoDB\BSON\Persistable&lt;/code&gt; injects a &lt;code&gt;__pclass&lt;/code&gt; variable into the document, which is a reference to the class that was used during serialization. It uses that reference to decide which class to unserialize into and overrides the type map.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="http://php.net/manual/en/class.mongodb-bson-persistable.php" rel="nofollow noreferrer"&gt;&lt;code&gt;MongoDB\BSON\Persistable&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;

